cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CC, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a new class of space-time block codes based on finite-field rank-metric codes and discusses their performance in terms of diversity order. This is a key topic in information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper presents a new decoding algorithm for the proposed codes that utilizes the algebraic structure of the underlying finite-field rank-metric codes and employs lattice-reduction-aided equalization. This is a topic related to systems and control. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Space-time block codes are used in wireless communication systems, which are a key component of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the proposed decoding algorithm, which has polynomial complexity in the matrix dimension. This is a topic related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new decoding algorithm for the proposed codes, which involves the use of lattice-reduction-aided equalization. This is a topic related to data structures and algorithms.
